e issues**\\n\\nSo, I’ve documented that isAvailable, but in the context of Native Image, I’m considering what happens if injector.inject throws an IllegalStateException because Class.forName can’t load, even if isAvailable is true. The cause might be UnsupportedFeature or ClassNotFound. If that’s the case, and caught ClassNotFound results in an empty bytes call for defineClass, it could lead to a ClassFormatError. I need to ensure that the bytes I provide for AlreadyLoadedType are valid and consider the implications if Class.forName fails to find the necessary metadata.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Generating valid bytes for classes**\\n\\nI’m considering if we can avoid invalid bytes by generating actual bytes for classes. However, dynamic class definitions aren’t supported in native environments, which complicates things. If it fails to load, it’s better to handle it within supported boundaries, but I’m not sure if that's the best approach. Maybe I could use a bootstrap JDK class like Object.class as a fallback to ensure I have something reliable. It’s worth exploring!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating bootstrap loader behavior**\\n\\nI’m testing behavior, specifically whether it returns an already loaded bootstrap type visible to the bootstrap loader. My focus is on injecting an existing type and ensuring the test's class name remains intact. It seems I should edit to use Object.class and think about renaming the method to `injectReturnsAlreadyLoadedBootstrapType`. Also, by removing the nested class, I can avoid any native metadata concerns, which means no need for an extra class.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_h8dykKxaDRGg8uWqUKutgsUd|fc_0a2e8251350d482e016a256d14bbd081969d97069070ef1974", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/net.bytebuddy/byte-buddy/1.8.15/src/test/java/net_bytebuddy/byte_buddy/ClassInjectorInnerUsingUnsafeTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "    void injectReturnsAlreadyLoadedTypeFromTargetClassLoader() {\n        TypeDescription typeDescription = TypeDescription.ForLoadedType.of(AlreadyLoadedType.class);\n        ClassInjector injector = new ClassInjector.UsingUnsafe(AlreadyLoadedType.class.getClassLoader());\n\n        try {\n            Map<TypeDescription, Class<?>> loaded = injector.inject(\n                    Collections.singletonMap(typeDescription, new byte[0]));\n\n            assertThat(loaded).containsEntry(typeDescription, AlreadyLoadedType.class);\n", "newText": "    void injectReturnsAlreadyLoadedBootstrapType() {\n        TypeDescription typeDescription = TypeDescription.ForLoadedType.of(Object.class);\n        ClassInjector injector = ClassInjector.UsingUnsafe.ofBootstrapLoader();\n\n        try {\n            Map<TypeDescription, Class<?>> loaded = injector.inject(\n                    Collections.singletonMap(typeDescription, new byte[0]));\n\n            assertThat(loaded).containsEntry(typeDescription, Object.class);\n"}, {"oldText": "\n    public static class AlreadyLoadedType {\n    }\n", "newText": ""}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 978, "output": 1113, "cacheRead": 27648, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 29739, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780837629606, "responseId": "resp_0a2e8251350d482e016a256cfe2fb88196bb3e963142783fc0"}}
